    "explanation": "<p>(a) Buna - S $$\\longrightarrow(P)$$ styrene, it is one of the monomer of buna - S, i.e. $$\\left[\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}_2\\right]$$</p>\n<p>(ii) Ethylene glycol $$\\longrightarrow(Q)$$, Trylene is made by the monomers, ethylene glycol</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0f8nvk3/5bf97a2a-6563-42a2-a669-b11a27de213e/0a5c6d30-65ff-11ef-9de2-c9be9960e8b4/file-jaoe38c1m0f8nvk4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0f8nvk3/5bf97a2a-6563-42a2-a669-b11a27de213e/0a5c6d30-65ff-11ef-9de2-c9be9960e8b4/file-jaoe38c1m0f8nvk4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"AIIMS 2019 Chemistry - Polymers Question 5 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>and terephtalic acid.</p>\n<p>(iii) Elastomer $$\\longrightarrow(\\mathrm{R})$$, Chloroprene is an example of elastomer.</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct match is :</p>\n<p>(i) - P, (ii) - Q, (iii) - R</p>",
